## Purpose

Produce a single dense health snapshot of the cluster covering nodes, pods, workloads, and disruption budgets. Read-only — never mutates cluster state.

## Arguments

This skill takes no positional arguments. If the user supplies one, respond with the missing/unknown-argument error line defined in the Global flags section and stop.

## Skill flags

- `--since <duration>` — Only flag issues observed in the last N (e.g. `5m`, `1h`, `24h`). Default: no time filter.
- `--severity <critical|warning|info>` — Filter output to findings at or above the given severity. Default: include all.

## Workflow

Run `KSTACK_ROOT="{{ROOT_DIR}}" {{SKILL_DIR}}/scripts/snapshot` exactly once, forwarding every user-supplied flag verbatim. The script owns the full aggregation (kubectl fanout, severity scoring, rendering) and returns finished output on stdout.

Display stdout verbatim — no edits, no restructuring, no added commentary. If the user passed `--json`, wrap the body in a ```json fenced block; otherwise print as-is. Do not run additional kubectl calls — the script owns the full snapshot. Route follow-up questions to `/investigate <kind>/<namespace>/<name>`.

If the script exits non-zero, display its stderr verbatim and stop.
